OL,4,Cwoman in crash on smart motorway
OL,6,FDefence lawyers argued O'Sullivan
OL,7,Fcould not have caused the death of Ms
OL,8,FDhillon because the crash was
OL,9,F"inevitable" given that the car was
OL,10,Fstationary in the fast lane and the
OL,11,Fsmart motorway was not displaying any
OL,12,Fwarning signs to other motorists.
OL,14,FWhile acknowledging "something went
OL,15,Fwrong" with the motorway's safety
OL,16,Falert system, the prosecution argued
OL,17,FO'Sullivan still caused the death of
OL,18,FMs Dhillon by driving carelessly and
OL,19,F"at speed".
